HEADWORD: Idioticon
<hw>Id`i*ot"i*con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ belonging to a private man, private. See <er>Idiot</er>.]</ety>
<def>A dictionary of a peculiar dialect, or of the words and phrases
peculiar to one part of a country; a glossary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idiotish</ent>⟦br⟧
